        <bioghist id="ref8">
            <head>Historical/Biographical Note:</head>
            <p>Faygle Stern (c1904-1936), was a Jewish communist active in the Jewish Section of the International Workers Order, primarily as a teacher in the Yiddish shule movement in the Brownsville section of Brooklyn, New York. She was born in Ostroleka (a.k.a. Ostrolenka), Poland, came to the United States in 1921, and died in childbirth in January, 1936.</p>
            <p></p>
